          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-10-28 12:19:33" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>the motion of an object rolling back and forth or rolling about{N:001}</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to roll about</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to wallow</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>It is rare that one can use in a language the same or related terms for the rolling of a person in an epileptic fit and the wallowing of a pig in the mud. The first is chaotic and uncontrolled, while the second is both purposeful and slower.</Comments>
